<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-224-754  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 224 754.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  March 5 1990 v4 n9 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>DOD names executive CIM team. (Department of Defense, CorporateInformation Management for streamlining computer systems)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Poos, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Department of Defense (DOD) names a team of military andcivilian executives to develop a plan of action on the CorporateInformation Management (CIM) initiative, aimed at coordinating andconsolidating the large number of administrative data processing(ADP) systems at DOD.andP;  CIM will also review existing and neededsoftware and attempt to replace or redundant systems to meet DODfunding and personnel cutbacks.andP;  For example, one or two payrollsystems may replace the 27 automated payroll systems DOD currentlyuses.andP;  The complexity of the CIM team's task is multiplied by thefact that the DOD has over 600,000 ADP systems.andP;  The team willmeet monthly for one year and then publish its proposed CIMstructure.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Department of DefenseInformation Resources ManagementData ProcessingAdministrative ServicesStudyPlanning.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>